---
import BaseLayout from '@layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Heat & Glo at HGTV Designer Showcase | Press + Media" description="Heat & Glo as a featured fireplace partner for the HGTV Designer Showcase. Designer-selected installations, editorial context, and the products that earn specification in nationally recognized design projects." noIndex={true}>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="relative mb-0 -mx-4 overflow-hidden">
    <img
      src="https://hearthnhome.getbynder.com/transform/21e1d116-6c89-445a-be2c-e1f30076c513/Toll-Bowman-Twilight-Mod_interior_cmyk_hi-res-jpg?io=transform:fill,width:1920,height:680"
      alt="Heat & Glo showcase installation — designer-quality contemporary fireplace in an HGTV featured home"
      class="w-full h-[600px] md:h-[420px] object-cover"
      loading="eager"
    />
    <div class="absolute inset-0 flex items-end pb-12 px-8" style="background: linear-gradient(to top, rgba(0,0,0,0.82) 0%, rgba(0,0,0,0.50) 55%, rgba(0,0,0,0.08) 100%);">
      <div class="max-w-page mx-auto text-white">
        <p class="uppercase tracking-wide text-sm font-semibold mb-2" style="color: #f97316;">Press + Media &rarr; HGTV Designer Showcase</p>
        <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold max-w-3xl leading-tight">Heat & Glo at the HGTV Designer Showcase.</h1>
        <p class="mt-4 text-lg max-w-2xl text-white/90">A featured fireplace partner for HGTV's national designer showcase, where the country's top residential designers build the rooms they want to build. 2024.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <main class="max-w-page mx-auto px-4 py-12">

    <!-- Direct answer lede -->
    <section class="mb-12 max-w-3xl">
      <p class="text-xl text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed">Heat & Glo was a featured fireplace partner for the HGTV Designer Showcase in 2024. Designer-selected Heat & Glo units appeared across showcase rooms, installed by the participating designers as part of their featured room presentations. The partnership represents both editorial credibility and specifier trust: the designers chose Heat & Glo because it is what they specify in their actual projects.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- What the HGTV Designer Showcase is -->
    <section class="mb-14">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">What the HGTV Designer Showcase is</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <div>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">The HGTV Designer Showcase is one of the most-watched design events in American residential television. A roster of top interior designers each take responsibility for one room in a full-home installation, selecting every product, material, and finish that goes into that room. The result is a curated demonstration of what the best designers in the country specify when given full creative control and no budget ceiling.</p>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">The audience is the HGTV viewership: tens of millions of homeowners who watch the network because they take design seriously and are actively involved in their homes. This is not a passive audience. HGTV viewers research brands, visit showrooms, and make purchase decisions influenced by what they see on the network.</p>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed">For a fireplace brand, placement in the Designer Showcase is particularly meaningful. The showcase rooms are high-design installations where the fireplace is a featured design element, not an afterthought. When a designer chooses Heat & Glo for a showcase room, that choice is visible to every viewer who watches the showcase episode and every viewer who sees the resulting press coverage.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="rounded-lg p-6" style="background: #f9f5f0; border: 1px solid #e8ddd3;">
            <p class="font-semibold mb-3">Why designers specify Heat & Glo in showcase projects</p>
            <ul class="space-y-3 text-sm text-neutral-700">
              <li class="flex gap-2 items-start"><span class="mt-0.5" style="color: #c44a08;">+</span> <span>Direct-vent design enables fireplace placement on any wall without chimney constraints, critical in a showcase setting where the room design comes first.</span></li>
              <li class="flex gap-2 items-start"><span class="mt-0.5" style="color: #c44a08;">+</span> <span>Contemporary linear configurations including the Mezzo and Primo II families suit the clean geometry of high-design interiors.</span></li>
              <li class="flex gap-2 items-start"><span class="mt-0.5" style="color: #c44a08;">+</span> <span>See-through configurations allow designers to place fire as a partition element between adjacent spaces.</span></li>
              <li class="flex gap-2 items-start"><span class="mt-0.5" style="color: #c44a08;">+</span> <span>Traditional configurations including the True family hold up against stone, tile, and full architectural mantels without requiring visual compromise.</span></li>
              <li class="flex gap-2 items-start"><span class="mt-0.5" style="color: #c44a08;">+</span> <span>ProAdvantage trade support means designers get the CAD files, spec sheets, and technical help a high-profile installation requires.</span></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Inline image -->
    <section class="mb-14 -mx-4">
      <img src="https://hearthnhome.getbynder.com/transform/937081fe-73df-4957-a0ec-8c5a1bfa3a05/HNG-Primo-II_60-2_2?io=transform:fill,width:1920,height:480" alt="Heat & Glo Primo II 60 linear gas fireplace in showcase-quality contemporary room" class="w-full h-[420px] md:h-[280px] object-cover" />
    </section>

    <!-- Inline editorial: designer-quality installation -->
    <section class="mb-10">
      <img src="https://hearthnhome.getbynder.com/transform/356c3756-554f-4d31-8bcf-328c48f813d9/SFE_Inception_Wescott_BWBirch_Halston_Room_1472x1110?io=transform:fill,width:1200,height:680" alt="SimpliFire Inception fireplace in a designer-quality room with birch logs and contemporary surround" class="w-full h-72 md:h-96 object-cover rounded-lg my-8" />
    </section>

    <!-- What designers look for in a showcase fireplace -->
    <section class="mb-14">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">What a designer needs from a showcase fireplace</h2>
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">A showcase room is designed for photography and broadcast. Every detail is deliberate. The fireplace in a showcase room is not selected for price. It is selected because it executes the design intent at the required scale and quality level, and because the installation can be executed cleanly within the project's timeline.</p>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">That last point matters more than it might seem. A showcase project has a hard deadline: the filming date. A fireplace that cannot be reliably specified, delivered, and installed within that window is not a viable option regardless of its design credentials. Heat & Glo's authorized dealer network and the ProAdvantage trade program exist specifically to support the kind of project-management reliability that high-profile installations require.</p>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed">For the designer, the combination of design flexibility and installation reliability is the value. A fireplace that can go anywhere in the room (direct-vent, no chimney requirement), that comes in the right size and configuration for the design (linear, traditional, see-through, outdoor), and that can be installed on schedule by a qualified local dealer, is what gets specified in a room where failure is not an option.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Inline editorial: see-through configuration in showcase setting -->
    <section class="mb-10">
      <img src="https://hearthnhome.getbynder.com/transform/2ea93327-a5bf-4bf1-9a89-65559689f3c1/Corner_Angle_Roomshot_180613_Swanson_0264-tif?io=transform:fill,width:1200,height:680" alt="Heat & Glo corner fireplace installation in a designer living room" class="w-full h-72 md:h-96 object-cover rounded-lg my-8" />
    </section>

    <!-- CTA band mid-page -->
    <section class="rounded-lg p-8 mb-12" style="background: #c44a08;">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-between gap-6">
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">Design professional? Join ProAdvantage.</h2>
          <p class="text-white/85 mt-1">CAD files, spec sheets, trade pricing, and a dedicated help desk for interior designers, architects, and builders.</p>
        </div>
        <a href="/pro/" style="background: #fff; color: #c44a08; padding: 0.75rem 1.75rem; border-radius: 0.375rem; font-weight: 700; white-space: nowrap; text-decoration: none; display: inline-block;">ProAdvantage</a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Products that appear in designer-quality installations -->
    <section class="mb-14">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">The configurations designers specify</h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-700 max-w-2xl mb-8">The Heat & Glo product families that appear in high-design editorial contexts are the ones that offer both visual flexibility and installation precision. These are the configurations that work in a showcase setting.</p>
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <a href="/fireplaces/gas/" class="group block border rounded-lg overflow-hidden hover:border-orange-500 hover:shadow-md transition">
          <img src="https://hearthnhome.getbynder.com/transform/d46ab388-275f-4983-b659-7c4cd454dcf5/img-pdp-mezzo-room-?io=transform:fill,width:720,height:420" alt="Heat & Glo Mezzo series linear gas fireplace with ribbon flame and crystal glass media on brick wall" class="w-full h-52 object-cover" />
          <div class="p-5">
            <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wide text-neutral-500 font-semibold mb-1">Contemporary linear</p>
            <p class="font-semibold group-hover:text-orange-700 transition">Gas Fireplaces &mdash; Mezzo + Primo II</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mt-2">Thin-frame contemporary geometry in five sizes. The configuration most frequently specified in clean-line high-design rooms. Linear ribbon flame, wide glass, full-width visual depth.</p>
          </div>
        </a>
        <a href="/fireplaces/see-through/" class="group block border rounded-lg overflow-hidden hover:border-orange-500 hover:shadow-md transition">
          <img src="https://hearthnhome.getbynder.com/transform/937081fe-73df-4957-a0ec-8c5a1bfa3a05/HNG-Primo-II_60-2_2?io=transform:fill,width:720,height:420" alt="Heat & Glo contemporary linear fireplace in open-plan room with angled staircase" class="w-full h-52 object-cover" />
          <div class="p-5">
            <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wide text-neutral-500 font-semibold mb-1">Partition element</p>
            <p class="font-semibold group-hover:text-orange-700 transition">See-Through Fireplaces</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mt-2">One firebox, two adjacent spaces. The configuration designers choose when fire is meant to work as a room divider or a shared visual anchor between a living space and a dining space.</p>
          </div>
        </a>
        <a href="/fireplaces/gas/" class="group block border rounded-lg overflow-hidden hover:border-orange-500 hover:shadow-md transition">
          <img src="https://hearthnhome.getbynder.com/transform/30bc701f-1f48-49fe-89e2-ace719cfeb71/HNG_True_gas-fireplace-hewing-hotel-lobby-2x-jpg?io=transform:fill,width:720,height:420" alt="Heat & Glo True series gas fireplace in an architectural hotel lobby setting with stone hearth" class="w-full h-52 object-cover" />
          <div class="p-5">
            <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wide text-neutral-500 font-semibold mb-1">Traditional architectural</p>
            <p class="font-semibold group-hover:text-orange-700 transition">Gas Fireplaces &mdash; True Series</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mt-2">Traditional proportions engineered for full architectural mantels, floor-to-ceiling stone, and hearth-room installations. The fireplace that disappears into the surround without disappearing from the design.</p>
          </div>
        </a>
        <a href="/accessories/" class="group block border rounded-lg overflow-hidden hover:border-orange-500 hover:shadow-md transition">
          <img src="https://hearthnhome.getbynder.com/transform/1463c616-67bb-453c-b704-3d065d548b0c/Fillmore_MantelShel?io=transform:fill,width:720,height:420" alt="Fillmore Mantel Shelf accessory from Heat & Glo" class="w-full h-52 object-cover" />
          <div class="p-5">
            <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wide text-neutral-500 font-semibold mb-1">Completion</p>
            <p class="font-semibold group-hover:text-orange-700 transition">Mantels, Surrounds + Accessories</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mt-2">Mantel shelves, stone surrounds, and accessory collections engineered specifically for Heat & Glo fireplace clearances. The finished detail work that completes a designer-quality installation.</p>
          </div>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Inline editorial: floating mantel / surround detail -->
    <section class="mb-10">
      <img src="https://hearthnhome.getbynder.com/transform/228d7240-a885-401b-9185-e854bdfb1cb1/SFE-Format-Floating-Mantel-Fireplace?io=transform:fill,width:1200,height:680" alt="SimpliFire Format fireplace with floating mantel in a showcase-quality installation" class="w-full h-72 md:h-96 object-cover rounded-lg my-8" />
    </section>

    <!-- The specifier relationship section -->
    <section class="mb-14">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">The designer-specifier relationship with Heat & Glo</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <div>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">Interior designers who specify Heat & Glo in showcase and editorial projects do so through the same trade infrastructure they use on residential projects: the ProAdvantage trade program and the authorized dealer network. The showcase installation process is not special-cased. The same spec sheets, the same CAD files, the same installation support that a designer uses on a client's home are the tools they use on a national showcase.</p>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed">This consistency matters. A brand that can support a showcase installation is a brand that can support a high-end residential project. The specifications are more demanding, the timeline is tighter, and the visibility is higher, but the process is the same. That reliability is what earns a brand repeated specification from the same design firm.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-3">For architects and designers: where to start</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">If you are specifying Heat & Glo for a project, the ProAdvantage trade program is the right entry point. Members receive access to CAD files formatted for common design software, specification-level product data, trade pricing through the authorized dealer network, and a dedicated trade help desk for installation questions.</p>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed">Registration takes minutes. The CAD library and spec documentation are available immediately after approval. Your local authorized dealer becomes the project's installation point of contact once the specification is finalized.</p>
          <div class="mt-4">
            <a href="/pro/" style="background: #c44a08; color: #fff; padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem; border-radius: 0.375rem; font-weight: 700; text-decoration: none; display: inline-block;">Join ProAdvantage</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Dealer CTA -->
    <section class="rounded-lg p-8 mb-12" style="background: #1a1a1a;">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-between gap-6">
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white">Find an authorized dealer for your project</h2>
          <p class="text-white/80 mt-1">Every authorized dealer carries current product and has completed HHT technical training. Your project's installation partner is in the network.</p>
        </div>
        <a href="/where-to-buy/" style="background: #c44a08; color: #fff; padding: 0.75rem 1.75rem; border-radius: 0.375rem; font-weight: 700; white-space: nowrap; text-decoration: none; display: inline-block;">Find a Dealer</a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Related coverage -->
    <section class="border-t pt-10 mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-5">Related coverage</h2>
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <a href="/press-and-media/today-show/" class="group block border rounded-lg p-5 hover:border-orange-400 hover:shadow-md transition">
          <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wide text-neutral-500 font-semibold">NBC Today Show</p>
          <p class="font-semibold mt-2 group-hover:text-orange-700 transition">Heat & Glo on Today</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mt-1">National broadcast coverage of Heat & Glo's role in American home renovation. 2025.</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/press-and-media/architectural-digest/" class="group block border rounded-lg p-5 hover:border-orange-400 hover:shadow-md transition">
          <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wide text-neutral-500 font-semibold">Architectural Digest</p>
          <p class="font-semibold mt-2 group-hover:text-orange-700 transition">Architectural Digest</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mt-1">Custom residential projects featured in AD specifying Heat & Glo for contemporary and traditional fireplace installations. 2024.</p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="border-t pt-6">
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500">
        <a href="/press-and-media/" class="underline">Back to press + media</a> &middot; <a href="/pro/" class="underline">ProAdvantage</a> &middot; <a href="/get-in-touch/" class="underline">Press inquiries</a>
      </p>
      <p class="text-xs text-neutral-400 mt-3">Note: specific Designer Showcase episode details, participating designers, and room names are pending confirmation from HHT's communications team. This page reflects Heat & Glo's verified 2024 HGTV Designer Showcase partnership. Contact <a href="/get-in-touch/" class="underline">press contact</a> for confirmed details.</p>
    </section>

  </main>
</BaseLayout>
